OL,3,CFamilies affected by baby loss come
OL,4,Ctogether to find comfort
OL,6,FThey also work to provide support
OL,7,Finformation and counselling services.
OL,9,FJo Nash, the charity's founder, says
OL,10,Fshe hopes the walk gave people an
OL,11,Fopportunity to form lasting
OL,12,Fconnections.
OL,14,F"Whilst Baby Loss Awareness Week is a
OL,15,Ffantastic opportunity to raise
OL,16,Fawareness, it is just that - one
OL,17,Fweek", she says.
OL,19,F"We hope those who know a bereaved
OL,20,Fparent will be mindful that, for them,
OL,21,Fit's not just a week - it's every day."
