OL,3,CFamilies affected by baby loss come
OL,4,Ctogether to find comfort
OL,6,F"What Philip's Footprints allowed me
OL,7,Fto do was have memories of my daughter
OL,8,Fthat without them I wouldn't have."
OL,10,FOn Wednesday 15 October, the end of
OL,11,FBaby Loss Awareness Week will be
OL,12,Fmarked with a Global Wave of Light -
OL,13,Fwhich invites families worldwide to
OL,14,Flight candles for one hour to remember
OL,15,Fall babies who have died too soon.
OL,17,FIn Jersey, this will take place at 7pm.
OL,19,FInformation about a range of support
OL,20,Fservices across the Channel Islands is
OL,21,Favailable here.
